heological thought, especially upon Bede's work. It then moves on toexplore the Old English translation in detail, setting it in the context of the English Benedictine reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChristian literature, English (Old). 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh  aAelfric's Life of Saint Basil the Great.  aAelfric.  aAnglo-Saxon England.  aBede.  aBenedictine reform.  aLatin.  aOld English.  aSaint Basil the Great.  ahagiography.  amedieval hagiography.  amedieval literature.  amedieval manuscripts.  amedieval monasticism.  amedieval scholarship.  amedieval studies.  amedieval theology.  areligious literature.  areligious texts.  atenth century.1 aCorona, Gabriella, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846158971423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846158971/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles